    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1338"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1338">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                    <gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the German Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador:</hi> Replying to your note of
                    to-day’s date in regard to an interview with Captain <persName>Boy-Ed</persName>
                    for the purpose of learning the reasons for the request for his recall, I regret
                    to say that I can only discuss the matter with you, and am unwilling to have an
                    interview on the subject with Captain <persName>Boy-Ed</persName>. In view of
                    the action already taken, I can see no good purpose in further discussion, as
                    the decision of this Government was reached only after long and careful
                    consideration.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
